race.comment: BELEGATO (1) loves this sprint trip with three wins and five placings from ten attempts and has won around this circuit. Strips fitter second-up and from the break gets a stack of weight relief with the 3kg claim. Looks the one they all have to run down. KING YOSHI (3) grows a leg for hoop Jones who has six wins from just seven steers. Racing high on confidence and is capable of testing his rivals again. PRE EMINENCE (4) is back from a spell but the form he showed when last in work was good enough for a race of this calibre. Can run a big race while fresh. PORT ERIN (8) is yet to miss a drum in four starts over this course and distance and looks a must for the multiples. TALTARNI FIELDS (2) rounds out the selections in a competitive affair.
